10. Observer Pattern Using C# Events
Real .NET projects usually use Events.

Publisher
public class PropertyService
{
    public event Action<string> PropertyAdded;

    public void AddProperty(string propertyName)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Property Added");

        PropertyAdded?.Invoke(propertyName);
    }
}
Subscriber
public class EmailService
{
    public void SendEmail(string propertyName)
    {
        Console.WriteLine(
          $"Email Sent For {propertyName}");
    }
}
Usage
var propertyService = new PropertyService();

var emailService = new EmailService();

propertyService.PropertyAdded +=
      emailService.SendEmail;

propertyService.AddProperty(
      "Luxury Villa");
Output:

Property Added

Email Sent For Luxury Villa
This is how Observer is often implemented in C#.

